          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p><sic><addressee>Rev. Isaak Leeser</addressee></sic>,
                                                  <placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>Smyrna</placeName>, <date>April 18.
                                                  1852</date></p>
                              <p>Sir!</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Yours of the <date>14.</date> inst came duly<lb/>
                                        to hand, as also did the 2 No: of The<lb/> occident.
                                        Enclosed I send you Three<lb/> Dollars subscription for the
                                        ensuing year,<lb/> for which you <del>pl</del> will please
                                        to send me<lb/> receipt by <sic>retourn</sic> of mail.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">When I look round and reflect,<lb/> how much the
                                        christian religion (and parti-<lb/>cular in this country)
                                        are doing to annex<lb/> Jews to her church, I am indeed
                                                  <sic>suprised</sic><lb/> to find you in your
                                        ,,Jewish advocate" com-<lb/>plaining, for not having
                                                  <sic>encouragments</sic> enough<lb/> from our
                                        fellow-Israelites in your different<lb/> works <del>of</del>
                                        on our holy religion. I think it<lb/> to be the duty of
                                        every true Israelite to<lb/> defend Judaism from the attacks
                                        daily made<lb/> by our opponents, and believe me, Rev.
                                        Sir,<lb/> were it in my power to obtain more
                                        subscri-<lb/>bers <del>to</del> for your valuable organ
                                        ,,the occident"<lb/> I would most assuredly do my best, to
                                        get<lb/> them. I am not at all surprised that<lb/> you
                                        hadn't any <sic>subsribers</sic> before, in this</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>State, as there is not more than me and<lb/> another Israelite
                                        living on this <placeName>Peninsula</placeName>,<lb/> and I
                                        regret to state that the latter<lb/> is married to a
                                        christian lady.â€”</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I am, Rev. Sir, with <sic>greatt</sic> respect</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Yours</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <persName role="author">Morris Stern</persName>
                              </p>
